# pjm-translator — AI Guidance

This project uses a shared instruction set in `.ai/`. Always read the relevant files
before starting work.

## Required reading

| File | When to read |
|------|--------------|
| `.ai/context/project.md` | Every session — project purpose, stack, architecture, conventions |
| `.ai/workflows/research-plan-act.md` | Every non-trivial task — mandatory workflow |
| `.ai/standards/coding.md` | Before writing or editing any Python code |
| `.ai/standards/testing.md` | Before writing or editing any test |
| `.ai/agents/developer.md` | When acting as implementation engineer |
| `.ai/agents/reviewer.md` | When acting as code reviewer |

## Quick rules

- **Python 3.14 + uv.** Do not change `pyproject.toml` without user approval.
- **snake_case** for all names; **PascalCase** for classes only.
- **Type hints + Google docstrings** on every public function.
- **Research → Plan → Act** before every implementation task.
- **⚠️ REQUIRES USER APPROVAL** before: adding/removing deps, deleting files,
  modifying CI/CD, or any destructive operation.
- Keep `main.py` thin; logic belongs in `src/`.
